result.name: Koon Thai Hai Nam Chicken

reviews.text:
I did not notice I was having Hai Nam Chicken at all - the chicken was like steak, dry and tasteless - until I dipped them into the Thai source.

Experts explained that good Hai Nam Chicken should form a layer of collagen during rapid cooling, but the chicken there had only oily skin instead.

The worst part, though came to the soup. Normally you got rice with chicken oil and Winter melon soup in an Hai Nam Chicken set, but there they seemed swapping the two! And we had a super oily soup, and a bowl of almost-plain rice.
Delicious Thai food but a bit expensive.
Yummy 😋😋😋
